B.  Grant Manager (national, 24 person-months,  July 2011-June 2013) 

4.  The grant manager should have at least 10 years of extensive experience in project 
management and implementation, and must possess excellent communication and coordination 
skills. The manager will:  

(i)  oversee day-to-day operation of the project; 
(ii)  prepare and submit required project plans, reports, implementation updates, and 
project briefs; 
(iii)  manage all staff and consultants; 
(iv)  lead the technical review and assessment of all project proposals and project 
design documents; 
(v)  approve all project procurements and disbursements; 
(vi)  lead the periodic results-focused monitoring and supervision of implementation of 
grant projects; 
(vii)  act as the main spokesperson of the project and lead project advocacy for “buy-
in” of project initiatives at various levels; 
(viii)  provide technical and administrative support to the interagency governing board; 
and 
(ix)  coordinate  with  development  agencies,  national  agencies,  and  other  major 
project stakeholders. 

C.   Program Officer and Knowledge Specialists (three national, 24 person-months each,  
July 2011-June 2013) 

5.  The consultants must have at least 5 years experience in project implementation and 
have the ability to serve as resource persons and organize training programs. Activities include: 

(i)  supervise, guide, and monitor implementation of LGU grant projects and LGU 
performance; 
(ii)  prepare plans, reports, and other project documents; 
(iii)  review, evaluate, and endorse LGU grant project proposals and project design 
documents; 
(iv)  provide specialist knowledge, on-the-job training, and technical assistance to 
LGUs; 
(v)  plan  and  manage  the  delivery  of  technical  training  and  capability-building 
activities for LGUs; and 
(vi)  liaise and coordinate with LGUs; the League of Cities, League of Municipalities, 
and the League of Provinces in the Philippines; the Department of Finance, the 
Bureau  of  Local  Government  Finance,  the  Department  of  Interior  and  Local 
Government, the Land Registration Authority, and other project stakeholders. 

D.  Senior Administration Officer (national, 24 person-months,  July 2011-June 2013)  

6.  The officer will have at least 5 years of experience in project implementation and the 
ability to serve as resource person and organize training programs. Activities include:  

(i)  administer all records, agreements, contracts, and official communications; 
(ii)  coordinate  all  provincial  travel  and  management  of  the  security  and  safety 
guidelines; 
(iii)  control the register of official reports, and provide reports as authorized;

