(iv)  provide overall management of the operations of the technical assistance (TA) 
communications systems, office supplies and services, office equipment, and 
backup of computer data; 
(v)  manage the TA payments, acquittal, and replenishment; 
(vi)  conduct internal audits of the administrative quality systems; 
(vii)  arrange annual external audit of accounts; 
(viii)  identify ways to improve the overall administration services for the management 
team; and  
(ix)  help  the grant manager  prepare  consultant contracts;  prepare  and  distribute 
documents; arrange meetings and appointments; control confidential documents; 
carry out secretarial functions for the interagency governing board in records 
managements; provide photocopying and binding, and distribute documents and 
organize board meetings; and maintain a library of photo documentation. 

E.  Finance Officer (national, 24 person-months,  July 2011-June 2013)  

7.  The officer will have at least 5 years of experience in project implementation and the 
ability to serve as a resource person and organize training programs. Activities include: 

(i)  operate the project accounting system in accordance with the quality manual for 
financial management; 
(ii)  prepare monthly and ad-hoc financial reports; 
(iii)  maintain the asset register; 
(iv)  prepare and issue cheques based on approved procurement orders; 
(v)  down load to LGUs approved fund requests into approved bank accounts and 
ensure  completeness  of  the  required  supporting  documents  to  support  the 
requests of funds; 
(vi)  monitor and process LGU acquittals of grant fund expenditures, and report to the 
grant manager; 
(vii)  provide  technical  assistance  to  the  LGUs  in  the  preparation  of  financial 
documents, reports, liquidations, and closure of subproject accounts; 
(viii)  prepare and process payroll and other salary related payments; 
(ix)  maintain cash flow prediction and request fund amounts appropriate for the next 
period; 
(x)  help with all audit operations; and 
(xi)  facilitate an account closure workshop for LGUs with completed subprojects and 
those nearing completion in preparation for the closure of books of accounts. 

F.  Geographic Information System Specialist (national, 5 person-months, intermittent,  
September 2011-October 2012) 

8.  The  specialist  must  have  at  least  5  years  experience  in  all  aspects  of  geographic 
information system (GIS) operation, extensive experience in different GIS software, preferably 
manifold, as well as training experience. Activities include: 

(i)  assess and identify training needs relative to progressive GIS and information 
technology capability building and enhancement appropriate to the participating 
LGU GIS needs, including specialized training programs; 
(ii)  provide  technical  advice  and  guidance  to  the  participating  LGUs  in  the 
